  +state(name, path, 'The Gem State', 'July 3, 1890')

  .intro
    p The Idaho state flag was first flown by the First Idaho Infantry during the Spanish-American War. Like many other infantries, including Montana, this flag featured the state seal on a field of blue.
    p Idaho’s seal is unique as the only state seal designed by a woman. Emma Edwards Green, a Boise artist, won the state seal design contest in 1891.
    p When it came time to adopt a state flag, the infantry flag was used. A banner reading “State of Idaho” was added below the seal.
    p The flag was officially adopted March 15, 1927.
    p In 1957, Green’s seal design was updated and repainted by artist Paul B. Evans.

